- To install this module you need to install the following EBox modules: eBox,
  Network, Firewall, Objects, UsersAndGroups and this debian testing packages:
  + Postfix with VDA patch applied.
  + postfix-tls
  + postfix-ldap
  + courier-pop
  + courier-imap
  + courier-pop-ssl
  + courier-imap-ssl
  + courier-authdaemon
  + courier-ldap

- Once all packages has been installed:
	
	./configure
	make install

  configure will autodetect EBox base path to install

- Update your sudoers file with the ebox-sudoers command.

- Copy conf/*.pem to /etc/postfix/sasl/, creating the directory if needed

- Execute as root (should be in $prefix/lib/ebox-mail/ ):
	./ebox-mail-ldap

- Do not services on startup, this module takes control all services:

mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXpostfix /etc/rc2.d/KXXpostfix
mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXcourier-authdaemon /etc/rc2.d/KXXcourier-authdaemon
mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXcourier-imap /etc/rc2.d/KXXcourier-imap
mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXcourier-imap-ssl /etc/rc2.d/KXXcourier-imap-ssl
mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXcourier-pop-ssl /etc/rc2.d/KXXcourier-pop-ssl
mv /etc/rc2.d/SXXcourier-pop /etc/rc2.d/KXXcourier-pop

- Stop all services if it's running.
